Preheat your #oven to 220°C. Halve the @green pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded). Slice into thin strips.

Pop the peppers on a #tray, drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

Roast the peppers on the top shelf of the #oven until charred and soft, ~{12-15%minutes}. Once cooked, remove and set aside (but keep the #tray).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{120%g} and half the @chorizo{60%g}(divided). Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1%tin} in a #colander. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the meat has browned, add the @peri peri seasoning{1} and half the garlic. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%tin}, black beans and @water{200%ml}. Stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} to dissolve. Add a pinch of @sugar{} and bring to the boil.

Simmer until the mixture has reduced slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the remaining @garlic clove{1}(minced) with the @olive oil{2%tbsp} and remaining chorizo.

Halve the @ciabatta{2}(halved, as if making a sandwich). Pop the ciabatta on a #baking tray{}, cut side up. Drizzle over the garlicky chorizo oil and use the back of a #spoon to press the chorizo into the ciabatta. Bake in your #oven until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir the roasted peppers into the stew. Taste and add salt, pepper and sugar if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if it's a bit thick.

Serve in #bowls with the chorizo ciabatta served alongside. Enjoy!